President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Nebraska due to flooding and has ordered federal aid to support state and local response efforts. The Department of Homeland Security, specifically the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA), will coordinate disaster relief efforts to help alleviate the suffering caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources as needed to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal government will provide 75 percent funding for emergency protective measures. Michael L. Parker has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.